                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1003">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bowen</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Caracas</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-04-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 8, 1902</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Bowen reports that the Venezuelan minister for foreign affairs states that
                    his Government knows nothing about a steamer of the New York and Bermudez
                    Company having been fired upon in San Juan River, and that the act was probably
                    committed by revolutionists.</p>
                <p>Mr. Bowen states that the steamer in question is at Trinidad, and suggests that
                    it might be advisable to send a United States war vessel there to investigate. *
                    * *)</p>
            </div>
